The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 3: India has entered into a pact with three major economies  Russia, Malaysia and Brazil  to ensure mutual flow of information on money laundering and terror funding. Negotiations to sign memoranda of understanding with more than 30 other countries is under process for enhancing international cooperation in fighting illegal routing of money for terror and hawala-like operations, a senior finance ministry official said.                             
	 New Delhi, Jan. 3: Steel maker SAIL has reported a 32 per cent growth in sales at 1.3 million tonnes in December 2009. Sales in the third quarter grew 23 per cent over the corresponding period last year on increase in sale of products consumed by the construction industry.                             
	 New Delhi, Jan. 3: The Prime Ministers economic adviser, C. Rangarajan, wants the RBI to remove excess money from the system to check rising prices as food inflation neared the decades high of 20 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 3: Insurance regulator IRDA is examining the possibilities of allowing cover for nuclear accidents, a step which assumes importance as India is expected to be a major player in this sector after the Indo-US nuclear deal is operationalised.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 3: Industry has asked the government to stem the price spiral by offloading foodgrain stocks in the open market. The rise in prices may restrict the monetary and fiscal space for manoeuvrability, CII director-general Chandrajit Banerjee said.                                                                                                                          
